Alony Hetz Soars Most in Two Years on Setting Extra Dividend

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-10-10T15:21:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/alony-hetz-poised-for-biggest-gain-in-two-years-on-dividend-plan.html
Alony Hetz Properties & Investments
Ltd. (ALHE)  surged the most in more than two years after the real-
estate investment company said it will pay an extra dividend and
set a dividend policy for 2012.  The shares jumped 8 percent to 17.67 shekels at the 4:30
p.m. close in  Tel Aviv , the biggest gain since August 2009. The
benchmark TA-25 Index soared 4.1 percent, the most since April
2009.  Ramat Gan, Israel-based Alony Hetz declared a dividend of
1.33 shekel a share, payable Nov. 13. Separately, the companyâ€™s
board adopted a  dividend policy  for next year to make four
quarterly payments of 0.20 shekel a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
